----------------------------------------------------------------------

This software contains:
- Empirical calibration constants derived from Ascend 910B4 NPU hardware
  measurements (msprof PipeUtilization / ArithmeticUtilization), used as
  the example calibration target. The methodology generalizes to any NPU
  with comparable profiling instrumentation.
- Architecture-sensitivity analysis methodology informed by publicly
  disclosed DaVinci microarchitecture documentation (HotChips 31, 2019)
  and the CANN 8.5 released toolkit.
- Optimization-ceiling analysis tooling that does NOT contain any vendor
  runtime source code or proprietary kernel implementations.

External dependencies (numpy, scipy, jinja2, pyyaml, pytest, ruff) are
distributed under their respective open-source licenses (BSD, MIT, etc.).
